terrapeer.vui.j3dui.utils.blocks
Class ActuationBlocks

java.lang.Object
  terrapeer.vui.j3dui.utils.blocks.ActuationBlocks
public class ActuationBlocks
extends java.lang.Object

These utilities are common building block utilities that were first introduced for the book's examples on "actuation" control.

Because these building blocks are rather specific in purpose they are included here as utilities instead of as general purpose building block classes in the framework core.

buildAbsoluteDragger

public static final void buildAbsoluteDragger(InputDragTarget target,
                                              AppView view,
                                              int mouseButtons,
                                              int mouseModifiers,
                                              int arrowModifiers)
Creates mouse and arrow drag sensors, enables the two sensor outputs according to button and modifier conditions, connects the combined drag inputs to a drag canceler, and connects it to the input drag target.

Arrow keys are inherently a relative device. To use them as an absolute device the mouse is used to establish an absolute reference position by means of an input move sensor connected to an input offset filter that filters the arrow sensor output.

Parameters:
target - Event target.
view - Source display. Never null.
mouseButtons - Mouse buttons enabling drag (Input.BUTTON_???).
mouseModifiers - Modifier keys enabling mouse drag (Input.MODIFIER_???).
arrowModifiers - Modifier keys enabling arrow drag (Input.MODIFIER_???).

Creates an input drag mapper for direct mapping, sets the source scale and dimension map, and connects the mapped drag input to the actuation target.

Parameters:
target - Event target.
dragScale - Display space scale factor.
dragMapX - Input X to actuation coordinate map (Mapper.DIM_???).
dragMapY - Input Y to actuation coordinate map (Mapper.DIM_???).
cumulative - True if drag actions are cumulative.
Returns:
New input drag mapper.
